# @param {String[][]} access_times
# @return {String[]}
def find_high_access_employees(access_times)
  # Organize access times by employee
  access_by_employee = Hash.new { |h, k| h[k] = [] }
  access_times.each { |name, time| access_by_employee[name] << time.to_i }

  # Find high access employees
  high_access_employees = access_by_employee.each_with_object([]) do |(name, times), acc|
    times.sort!
    times.each_with_index do |time, i|
      # Look for three or more accesses within a one-hour period
      range_end = i + 2 # Checking the current and next two times for a match within an hour
      if range_end < times.size && (times[range_end] - time < 100 || (times[range_end] / 100 == time / 100 && times[range_end] % 100 - time % 100 <= 59))
        acc << name
        break # Stop checking this employee as they've already qualified
      end
    end
  end

  high_access_employees
end
